article.headline: Brown 100, Harvard 83
article.story: PROVIDENCE, R.I. (AP) -- Patrick Powers scored 27 points as Brown defeated Harvard 100-83 Saturday night. Kevin Rogus led the Crimson (4-21, 3-9 Ivy) with 28 points, including six 3-pointers, and Matt Stehle added 22. Brown (13-12, 9-3), leading 16-14 early in the first half, opened up the game with a 29-10 run over the next 8:17 for a 45-24 lead with 6:59 to play. Powers led the rally by scoring 11 points, including three 3-pointers. Harvard pulled to 74-56 with 11:20 remaining, but Brown built up its largest lead of the game when Jason Forte hit two free throws with 8:46 to play, giving the Bears an 82-56 edge. Forte finished the game with 24 points and 10 assists for Brown, while Jaime Kilburn added 17 points and pulled down 14 rebounds. Brown led 57-37 at halftime.
